<subSubSection id="C339651529611962FF75415C09EDB15C" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C369E29611962FF75415C09EDB15C" blockId="1.[151,1436,1810,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FF75415C0900B174" bold="true" box="[198,326,1850,1876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Habitus very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29611962FDD9415D0A98B174" box="[618,734,1851,1876]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Eudorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FDD9415D0A98B174" box="[618,734,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Eudorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but pereiopod 
<number id="3DEB24B929611962FC29415C0BEFB174" box="[922,937,1850,1876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
absent in both sexes, males with strongly developed penial lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C339651529611962FF7541EC0CBBB184" box="[198,1277,1930,1956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9C369E29611962FF7541EC0CBBB184" blockId="1.[151,1436,1810,2036]" box="[198,1277,1930,1956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FF7541EC0915B184" bold="true" box="[198,339,1930,1956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new genus is named after the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29611962FC8341ED0BE2B184" box="[816,932,1931,1956]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Eudorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FC8341ED0BE2B184" box="[816,932,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Eudorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which it strongly resembles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C339651529611961FF7541D409FEB7D2" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9C369E29611961FF7541D40996B722" blockId="1.[151,1436,1810,2036]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,498]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FF7541D40979B1EC" bold="true" box="[198,319,1970,1996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Remarks.</emphasis>
The penial lobes between the pereiopods 
<number id="3DEB24B929611962FC9941D40B7EB1EC" box="[810,824,1970,1996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
within the order 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29611962FBB241D40C28B1EC" box="[1025,1134,1970,1996]" class="Malacostraca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Cumacea</taxonomicName>
vary a lot. There are conical forms in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29611962FE1B41BD0A0CB1D4" box="[424,586,2011,2036]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Archaeocuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29611962FE1B41BD0A0CB1D4" box="[424,586,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Archaeocuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29611962FD1D41BC0B0AB1D4" box="[686,844,2010,2036]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lampropidae</taxonomicName>
/Archaeocumatidae), or two cylindrical penes with a copulatory organ in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FDAF46FE0A89B691" box="[540,719,152,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nannastacidae" genus="Campylaspenis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FDAF46FE0A89B691" box="[540,719,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Campylaspenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FC8A46FE0BAFB692" box="[825,1001,152,178]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nannastacidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nannastacidae</taxonomicName>
). The penial lobes in the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FF2446A60908B6F9" box="[151,334,192,217]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Pseudeudorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FF2446A60908B6F9" box="[151,334,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Pseudeudorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are cylindrical with two relatively long subterminal pappose setae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B6F29621961FB2346A60985B722" author="Watling" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Watling, L. &amp; McCann, L. (1997) Cumacea. Taxonomic Atlas of thr Benthic Fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and Western Santa Barbara Channel. Volume 11 - The Crustacea Part 2, 121 - 180." type="book chapter" year="1997" yearSuffix="p">
Watling and McCann, 
<number id="3DEB24B929621961FF24468E0892B722" box="[151,212,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1997.0">1997</number>
, Figure 2.21, p. 
<number id="3DEB24B929621961FE20468E0985B722" box="[403,451,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="157.0">157</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9C369E29621961FF75477609FEB7D2" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B6F29621961FF754776090BB70A" author="Day" box="[198,333,272,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Day, J. (1978) Southern African Cumacea, part 3. Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatiodae. The Annals of the South African Museum 76 (3), 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">
Day (
<number id="3DEB24B929621961FEB447760902B70A" box="[263,324,272,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B6F29621961FE3647760A7AB70A" author="Ledoyer" box="[389,572,272,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1988) Cumaces (Crustacea) profonds de la ragion de l'ile de Mayotte, Canal de Mozambique, Ocean Indien (Campagne Bemthedi, 1977). MESOGEE 48, 131 - 172." type="journal article" year="1988">
Ledoyer (
<number id="3DEB24B929621961FE4547760A75B70A" box="[502,563,272,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
were not convinced that the presence of penial lobes is a sufficient difference to warrant the erection of a new genus or family. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B6F29621961FC97475E0C3EB772" author="Watling" box="[804,1144,312,338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Watling, L. &amp; McCann, L. (1997) Cumacea. Taxonomic Atlas of thr Benthic Fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and Western Santa Barbara Channel. Volume 11 - The Crustacea Part 2, 121 - 180." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Watling and McCann (
<number id="3DEB24B929621961FB81475E0C29B772" box="[1074,1135,312,338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
followed this statement, but they made a restriction and stated that “this view may change as more of these aberrant forms are discovered”. They argued that a single character is not sufficient enough to erect a new genus. However, the second character of the new genus, missing pereiopod 
<quantity id="4CDB9B7B29621961FD7747D60AB4B7EA" box="[708,754,432,458]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
both sexes, makes the new genus unique and easy to distinguish from 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FE8E47BE09F7B7D1" box="[317,433,472,497]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Eudorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FE8E47BE09F7B7D1" box="[317,433,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Eudorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
